HEADWORD: Self-examinant
<hw>Self`-ex*am"i*nant</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who
examines himself; one given to self-examination.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The humiliated <qex>self-examinant</qex> feels that there is evil
in our nature as well as good.</q> <rj><qau>Coleridge.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Self-examination</ent>⟦br⟧
